This paper proposes a novel recurrent architecture for natural language processing tasks, which involves integrating tree structures into recurrent neural networks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of ordered neurons to model the hierarchy of constituents, which is a technique that could be relevant to other machine learning tasks beyond language modeling. Therefore, the paper could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
